nodes.text: Star Tours Flight 114 was the designation of two Star Tours flights:

The first was a StarSpeeder 1000 flight to Corellia by the Star Tours travel agency at the time of the Raid at Spaceport THX1138. The flight was set to arrive at 1435 hours at Gate 2F, but was delayed, moving its scheduled departure time from 1530 hours to 1610.
The second was a non-stop StarSpeeder 3000 flight to Endor offered to passengers by the Star Tours travel agency around 4.3 ABY.
